.TH "HTMLIMAGEELEMENT.CURRENTSRC" "3JS" "November 7, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLImageElement.currentSrc \- HTMLImageElement: currentSrc property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]currentSrc\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]HTMLImageElement\f[R] interface indicates the URL of the image
selected by the browser to load.
.SH VALUE
A string indicating the full URL of the image currently selected by the
browser to load.
If the image uses the \f[CR]srcset\f[R] attribute, \f[CR]currentSrc\f[R]
lets you determine which image from the set of provided images was
selected by the browser.
The property\(cqs value is unrelated to whether the image has
successfully loaded or not.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Testing which image is loaded
In this example, two different sizes are provided for an image of a
clock.
One is 200px wide and the other is 400px wide.
The \f[CR]sizes\f[R] attribute is provided to indicate that the image
should be drawn at 50% of the document width if the viewport is under
400px wide; otherwise, the image is drawn at 90% width of the document.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]img\f[R]
  src=\(dq/en\-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/img/clock\-demo\-400px.png\(dq
  alt=\(dqClock\(dq
  srcset=\(dq
    /en\-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/img/clock\-demo\-200px.png 200w,
    /en\-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/img/clock\-demo\-400px.png 400w
  \(dq
  sizes=\(dq(width \f[B]<\f[R]= 400px) 50%, 90%\(dq />
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] clockImage = document.querySelector(\(dqimg\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] p = document.createElement(\(dqp\(dq);

p.textContent = clockImage.currentSrc.endsWith(\(dq200px.png\(dq)
  ? \(dqUsing the 200px image!\(dq
  : \(dqUsing the 400px image.\(dq;
document.body.appendChild(p);
.EE
.SS Result
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]HTMLImageElement.src\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]HTMLImageElement.srcSet\f[R]
